                  </hi>. I apprehended the prisoner at 112, Bermondsey-street—I produce the certificate of marriage, which I have examined at the parish church, at Halifax—it is correct—I have another certificate from St. Mary's, Southwark—they are true copies—(<hi rend="italic">read.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> When did you get this certificate from Halifax? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Mrs. Clegg, the first wife, gave it to me—I have compared it with the book at the church—I saw the clerk—he read the book first, and I held the certifi<lb></lb>cate—then he read the certificate, and I the book.</p>
